❗️Clear division of powers and enhanced supervision of decisions on the ground. Draft Law No. 4298 on local state administrations is ready for consideration, — Head of the State Power Organization Committee, Olena Shuliak. The decentralization reform transferred resources and powers to the local level. However, the question of responsibility for the adopted decisions remains open. The document is aimed at solving this problem, the parliamentarian emphasized.

The act is supposed to regulate the rights and functions of the MDA, in particular:

- granting the heads of the MDA and their deputies the status of civil servants;
- creating a personnel reserve;
- coordination of MDA activities of territorial divisions of central executive bodies;
- ensuring the supervision of the legality of actions of local government;
- a balanced appointment system for the dismissal of MDA heads;
- a clear division of powers of the Regional State Administration and the RDA. 📲DetailsTelegram/ Facebook/ Site/Instagram/ Twitter

